GNS/MC was synthesized by solid state nanocasting method

MC was attributed to the contributions of residual transition
metal (Ni and Fe) entities, nitrogen-doped defect-rich gra-

In the quest of cost-effective air electrodes, Senthilkumar
et al. explored the possibility to use cobalt phosphate as effi-
cient bifunctional air electrode.
The authors synthesized
cobalt phosphate by simple precipitation followed by calci-
nation method and functionalize a carbon paper electrode.
The bifunctional electrocatalytic activity for ORR and OER
was evaluated in alkali electrolyte by rotating ring-disk elec-
trode (RRDE) method. The electron transfer number asso-
ciated with ORR was calculated to be
3.9 close to 4 which
suggests that ORR occurred through a four-electron transfer
pathway, thus avoiding the formation of hydrogen peroxide.

far from practical applications. Like in this last study, a typical
